.TH AGENTTEAMS 1 "April 2026" "agentteams" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
agentteams \- Generate a complete agent team for any project.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B agentteams [--description PATH] [--project PATH] [--framework NAME] [--output DIR] [--dry-run] [--overwrite] [--yes] [--no-scan] [--update] [--prune] [--check] [--scan-security] [--self] [--post-audit] [--auto-correct] [--enrich] [--security-offline] [--security-max-items N] [--security-no-nvd] [--version]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Generate a complete agent team for any project.
.PP
Given a project description file (.json or .md), agentteams analyzes the project goal, selects the right 4\-tier agent team, renders all agent files from templates, and writes them to the target project's .github/agents/ directory.
.PP
The generated team includes an orchestrator, nine governance agents, domain agents appropriate for the deliverable type, and one workstream expert per project component.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-description, \-d PATH
Project description file (.json or .md). Required unless \-\-self is used.
.TP
.B \-\-project, \-p PATH
Project directory to scan and use as base (overrides existing_project_path in description)
.TP
.B \-\-framework, \-f NAME
Target framework: copilot\-vscode, copilot\-cli, claude (default: copilot\-vscode)
.TP
.B \-\-output, \-o DIR
Output directory for agent files. Default: <project>/.github/agents/
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Show what would be generated without writing files
.TP
.B \-\-overwrite
Overwrite existing agent files without prompting
.TP
.B \-\-yes, \-y
Non\-interactive: answer yes to all prompts
.TP
.B \-\-no\-scan
Disable project directory scanning
.TP
.B \-\-update
Re\-render drifted files and emit new agents added to the taxonomy. Preserves manually\-filled \\(lCMANUAL:*\\(rC values from existing files. Removed agents are reported but not deleted (use \-\-prune to remove them).
.TP
.B \-\-prune
Used with \-\-update: also delete agent files that are no longer part of the team.
.TP
.B \-\-check
Check for template drift and structural changes without writing any files (exit code 1 if drift or structural changes are detected)
.TP
.B \-\-scan\-security
Scan generated agent files for security issues (PII, credentials, unresolved placeholders)
.TP
.B \-\-self
Operate on the module's own agent team using .github/agents/_build\-description.json
.TP
.B \-\-post\-audit
Run a post\-generation audit after emit. Performs static checks (unresolved placeholders, YAML integrity, required\-agent coverage) and, if the `gh` CLI is authenticated, an AI\-powered conflict and presupposition review via GitHub Models (Claude Sonnet 4.6).
.TP
.B \-\-auto\-correct
After \-\-post\-audit finds issues, invoke the standalone `copilot` CLI in non\-interactive mode to repair generated team files, then rerun the audit.
.TP
.B \-\-enrich
After generating the team, scan for default template elements (unresolved \\(lCMANUAL:*\\(rC placeholders, underdeveloped sections, incomplete tool metadata) and attempt context\-aware auto\-enrichment. Exports a defaults\-audit.csv to the references/ directory. Combine with \-\-post\-audit to also run AI\-powered enrichment.
.TP
.B \-\-security\-offline
Use cached security vulnerability snapshot only (no network fetch) when rendering security intelligence references.
.TP
.B \-\-security\-max\-items N
Maximum number of current vulnerabilities to include in generated security references (default: 15)
.TP
.B \-\-security\-no\-nvd
Skip NVD CVSS enrichment (avoids ~7 s per CVE rate\-limit sleep). CISA KEV + EPSS data are still fetched.
.TP
.B \-\-version
show program's version number and exit
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Error: validation failure, file not found, drift detected (with \fB--check\fR), or security issues (with \fB--scan-security\fR).
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Generate a VS Code Copilot agent team:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
agentteams \-\-description brief.json \-\-project /path/to/project
.fi
.RE
.PP
Generate for Copilot CLI without writing (dry run):
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
agentteams \-\-description brief.json \-\-framework copilot\-cli \-\-dry\-run
.fi
.RE
.PP
Re\-render drifted files after a template update:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
agentteams \-\-description brief.json \-\-update
.fi
.RE
.PP
Check for drift in CI (exits 1 if stale):
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
agentteams \-\-description brief.json \-\-check
.fi
.RE
.PP
Scan generated files for security issues:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
agentteams \-\-description brief.json \-\-scan\-security
.fi
.RE
.PP
Run post\-generation audit with AI review:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
agentteams \-\-description brief.json \-\-post\-audit
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
Full documentation: .UR https://jlcatonjr.github.io/agentteams/
.UE
